1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the capacity region of a two-way relay channel, which is a classic problem in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses a cooperative network with multiple users sharing a common resource, which is a common topic in networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper investigates the behavior of a system with an intermittently available relay, which falls under the scope of systems and control. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions the exchange of messages between pairs of users, which could involve multimedia data. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - Although not the main focus of the paper, the intermittently available relay could be vulnerable to security attacks, making this paper relevant to cryptography and security.
